          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1701944452472-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1701944452472-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the softened onion and cook for 1 min further, then set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1701944458270-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1701944458270-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1701944458270-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1701944458270-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1701944458270-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> gem lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and separate the <strong>outer leaves</strong>, then finely shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong></p><p>Drain and finely dice your <strong>pineapple</strong></p><p>Tip: Don’t chuck pineapple juice down the drain. Instead, add it to your smoothies, cakes or marinades!</p><p>Combine the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> diced pineapple </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) in a bowl with plenty of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701944466232-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1701944466232-x400.jpg",
